{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"title":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"}],"externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"text":" depending to size classes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"text":" inside one object.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a font token exists with its value depending to the size class, it must be packed in such ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(compact:regular:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/compact","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/regular"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/fontToken(for:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/isEqual(_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token displayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let bold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size850, lineHeight: lineHeight1050, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing850)","        let bold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: size1450, lineHeight: lineHeight1850, weight: weight700, letterSpacing: letterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.bold850, regular: FontRawTokens.bold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var displayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.bold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The case of this "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains ","type":"text"},{"code":"FontCompositeRawToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" kit.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Since","type":"aside"}]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSTokensSemantic/documentation/OUDSTokensSem